# Hey! PNU — Cursor Project Rules

## What this project is
A one-stop platform for foreign students at Pusan National University (PNU),
covering: application info, campus onboarding, academic tools (course/graduation
tracking), AI assistant, emergency support, and community. Multilingual (KO/EN/ZH/JA/VI).
See PROJECT_CONTEXT.md for full feature list and BACKEND_STATUS.md for what's built.

## Stack (do not deviate without asking)
- Frontend: React (JS), HTML/CSS
- Backend: Node.js
- Database: PostgreSQL
- AI integrations: OpenAI/Claude APIs, Google AI Studio (Gemini) for notice summarization/translation

## How to work with me
- Before implementing a feature, check BACKEND_STATUS.md and the relevant route/model
  files instead of assuming nothing exists yet.
- Prefer extending existing patterns (naming, folder structure, error handling) over
  introducing new ones. If you must introduce a new pattern, say so explicitly and why.
- Keep endpoints RESTful and grouped by domain (auth, users, courses, scholarships,
  checklist, emergency, community, notices).
- All user-facing strings must go through the i18n layer — never hardcode Korean or
  English text in components or API responses that reach the client.
- For anything touching visa, immigration, banking, or legal info: flag it clearly as
  "needs human/legal review" rather than presenting it as fully verified.
- After finishing a feature, propose an update to BACKEND_STATUS.md (I'll confirm before
  you write it) so the status doc stays accurate.
- Ask before adding new npm dependencies for something a current dependency already covers.

## Things to avoid
- Don't invent database schema for a table that might already exist — check /db or
  /prisma (whichever we're using) first.
- Don't silently change API response shapes consumed by the frontend.
